00:28:23.370 --> 00:28:26.700
to do this in a big-scaled
way that has I think been one

00:28:26.700 --> 00:28:30.550
of the most powerful voices saying,
"We're approaching this right."

00:28:30.550 --> 00:28:34.340
So I think that as we think
about what's next in this space,

00:28:34.340 --> 00:28:37.010
in my mind it is time
for a transition.

00:28:37.010 --> 00:28:40.680 position:56%
And I think the projects that
Christine gave a really nice history

00:28:40.680 --> 00:28:44.240
of were groundbreaking,
and they were powerful,

00:28:44.240 --> 00:28:46.210
and they proved that we can do it.

00:28:46.210 --> 00:28:48.310
And I think that was a
really important thing

00:28:48.310 --> 00:28:50.630
for libraries to go do and prove.

00:28:50.630 --> 00:28:52.680
But I think they also proved
something else which is

00:28:52.680 --> 00:28:57.060
that they demonstrated that this is
work that just screams for scale.

00:28:57.060 --> 00:28:59.750
Once you build these
capacities you should share them

00:28:59.750 --> 00:29:02.640
because it's very easy to
reuse them and to share them.

00:29:02.640 --> 00:29:05.280 position:56%
And so I think that we are
benefitting from the lessons learned

00:29:05.280 --> 00:29:08.730
from those projects in that the
projects that I'm going to talk

00:29:08.730 --> 00:29:11.050
about have been conceived in a way

00:29:11.050 --> 00:29:13.560
that beg-scaling from
the very beginning.

00:29:13.560 --> 00:29:15.420
And I said this at PLA
last week I'm going

00:29:15.420 --> 00:29:16.720 position:56%
to start saying it every time I talk

00:29:16.720 --> 00:29:20.660
about this I think we are talking
precisely about building components

00:29:20.660 --> 00:29:22.870
of a national digital
platform for libraries.

00:29:22.870 --> 00:29:24.350
This is precisely that.

00:29:24.350 --> 00:29:25.800
And we're starting with ebooks.

00:29:25.800 --> 00:29:29.020
And I think this will show
that we have the capacity

00:29:29.020 --> 00:29:32.830
to build capabilities that can
very quickly expand beyond ebooks.

00:29:32.830 --> 00:29:35.840 position:56%
And I would say even this year we're
likely to be able to handle things

00:29:35.840 --> 00:29:38.930
like audio And it will very
quickly be clear that this is not

00:29:38.930 --> 00:29:42.030
about ebooks, this is about
delivering library content

00:29:42.030 --> 00:29:44.570
to patrons on library-owned
infrastructure.

00:29:44.570 --> 00:29:47.870
So this is in my mind a first foray

00:29:47.870 --> 00:29:50.240
into building the national
digital platform for libraries.

00:29:50.240 --> 00:29:51.990
And I think that's how
we should conceive of it.

00:29:51.990 --> 00:29:55.740
So I want to give another shout out
