public circulating libraries

00:31:29.230 --> 00:31:32.430
to also benefit academic
and school libraries

00:31:32.430 --> 00:31:33.800
and special libraries as well.

00:31:33.800 --> 00:31:38.480 position:56%
And I think that ReadersFirst offers
us a model and a vehicle, in part,

00:31:38.480 --> 00:31:41.070 position:56%
I think there are many organizations
that can and should contribute

00:31:41.070 --> 00:31:43.660
to this to continue
to move that forward

00:31:43.660 --> 00:31:46.710
and give libraries the
raw materials they need

00:31:46.710 --> 00:31:48.270
in order to own their service.

00:31:48.270 --> 00:31:50.470
And that really starts
with interoperability.

00:31:50.470 --> 00:31:54.560
And so I think that's a critical
underpinning of all of this work.

00:31:54.560 --> 00:31:56.280
So with that I'm going to start by,

00:31:56.280 --> 00:31:58.240
I mean most of you know these
projects so I'm going to try

00:31:58.240 --> 00:31:59.540
to move through it quickly.

00:31:59.540 --> 00:32:04.590
As you probably know the grant in
2012 that was awarded by the IMLS

00:32:04.590 --> 00:32:08.500
to create the Library Simplified
Project now named SimplyE

00:32:08.500 --> 00:32:12.610
as the product that came out of
that has been I think, you know,

00:32:12.610 --> 00:32:14.690
we've been working
hard for three years.

00:32:14.690 --> 00:32:16.700
My colleague and partner
