00:37:25.050 --> 00:37:27.770
So the next series in
this project was LEAP,

00:37:27.770 --> 00:37:30.690 position:56%
the Library eContent Access Project,
which you've all heard a lot about.

00:37:30.690 --> 00:37:34.050
This is basically the effort to
go further and build a backend

00:37:34.050 --> 00:37:37.100
to this system that would be
a library-owned marketplace,

00:37:37.100 --> 00:37:39.630
a library-centric marketplace
and distributor.

00:37:39.630 --> 00:37:43.340
So this is the whole right-hand
side of the six-part stack

00:37:43.340 --> 00:37:45.130
at the bottom of this page.

00:37:45.130 --> 00:37:47.320
I think this can be
built and up, hopefully,

00:37:47.320 --> 00:37:49.300
in a pilot version
this calendar year.

00:37:49.300 --> 00:37:51.300
So we're going to try
to push very quickly.

00:37:51.300 --> 00:37:53.990
Again, building on Christine's
point, we're learning

00:37:53.990 --> 00:37:56.200
from what others have done
that started before us.

00:37:56.200 --> 00:37:58.070
And so we're conceiving this right

00:37:58.070 --> 00:38:00.180
out of the gate as
a national platform.

00:38:00.180 --> 00:38:03.110
Every library in the country will
be free and we will encourage them

00:38:03.110 --> 00:38:07.550
